1. Physical therapy is efficient to treat musculoskeletal dysfunctions in sickle cell disease patients.
2. The efficiency of physical therapy in treating musculoskeletal dysfunctions in sickle cell disease patients is not dependent on the technique used.
3. Aquatic therapy showed a trend toward improvement in muscle strength in sickle cell disease patients.
